article.description: Fletcher Magee hit 5 of 7 from 3-point range and Wofford crushed Carver Bible College, 94-35 in its home opener Tuesday night.
article.headline: Wofford stays hot from 3, routs Carver Bible College, 94-35
article.linkText: Wofford stays hot from 3, routs Carver Bible College, 94-35
article.story: SPARTANBURG, S.C. -- Fletcher Magee hit 5 of 7 from 3-point range and Wofford crushed Carver Bible College, 94-35 in its home opener Tuesday night. The Terriers lost their season opener to No. 8 North Carolina, 77-68 and rebounded to knock off High Point, 68-60 before heading home to host the Cougars of the NCCAA for the first time. Magee shot 5 for 8 in the win over High Point and Wofford hot 12 of 25 from 3-point range as a team. Against Carver they hit 12 of 26 from distance (46.2 percent). Cameron Jackson, a preseason All-Southern Conference selection, came one rebound shy of his second straight double-double, finishing with 11 points and nine boards. Ryan Larson added 11 points off the bench. Jalan Strong finished with 11 points and was the lone Cougar to reach double-figure scoring.
